<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880921-0007 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Home Loan Bank In Dallas Picks Wood To Be Chief Regulator </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS GOVMT </CO><IN> BNK </IN><DATELINE> DALLAS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Billy C. Wood was named director of regulatory affairs for the Federal Home Loan Bank of Dallas, whose district includes the troubled thrift industry in Texas.    Mr. Wood, 48 years old, fills a vacancy created several months ago, when H. Joe Selby resigned. Mr. Wood has been managing director of the Los Angeles office of the Secura Group since 1987, and previously spent 25 years with the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency.    The Dallas bank also named James R. Voisinet as executive vice president and chief operating officer of the bank's financial group, which handles the banking side. He succeeds Jonathan Heffron, who left to become president of a New Hampshire savings and loan.    Mr. Voisinet, 57, has been president and chief executive officer of Troy andamp; Nichols Mortgage Co. in Monroe, La., since 1987 and previously was president and chief operating officer of National Gypsum Co.    The Dallas bank is the principal regulator and central bank for about 476 thrifts in Texas, Arkansas, Louisiana, Mississippi and New Mexico that are insured by the Federal Savings andamp; Loan Insurance Corp. </TEXT></DOC>